text: ['3.2.2  Export taxes and charges', "3.81.  In  Honduras,  export  tax  has  to  be  paid  on  coffee  and  some  minerals  (Table 3.11).  When registering a purchase with the Honduran Coffee Institute (IHCAFE), either for export or for sale on the domestic market, producers, coffee roasters and/or exporters have to pay US$9 per quintal of  green  coffee  to  the  IHCAFE.  This  sum  is  earmarked  for  paying  the  coffee  growers'  debt  and funding a trust to revitalize the sector.61 Coffee exports must also have an export certificate issued by the IHCAFE, which costs US$2.75 per bag (46 kg) of green coffee exported or US$3.25 per bag (46 kg) if the exporter has a debt with the IHCAFE.62 Exports, as well as sales of some minerals on", '55 PowerPoint presentation by PROHONDURAS.
